ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Lie in bed, feeling physically relaxed
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Lie in bed, feeling mentally relaxed
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Lie in bed with your thoughts ''turned off''
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Fall asleep at night in under 30 minutes
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Wake up at night fewer than 3 times
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Go back to sleep within 15 minutes of waking in the night
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Feel refreshed upon waking in the morning
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Wake after a poor night's sleep without feeling upset about it
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Indicate how confident you are that you can: Not allow a poor night's sleep to interfere with daily activities
Notes: 1= Not confident at all; 5= Very confident
